DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "niceTables.pl", "parserPopUp.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context('Numeric'); @x = (3,6,8,12); @y = (-2,-8,-12,-20); $popup = DropDown(['The relationship is linear','The relationship is not linear'],0);
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Is there a linear relationship in the table?
>> [@DataTable( [ [[PGML('[`x`]'), rowbottom => '2', midrule => '1',], PGML('[`y`]'), ], [PGML('[`[$x[0]]`]'), PGML('[`[$y[0]]`]'), ], [PGML('[`[$x[1]]`]'), PGML('[`[$y[1]]`]'), ], [PGML('[`[$x[2]]`]'), PGML('[`[$y[2]]`]'), ], [PGML('[`[$x[3]]`]'), PGML('[`[$y[3]]`]'), ], ], align => 'rl', valign => 'middle',);@]* <<
[_]{$popup}{5}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION The changes in [`x`] from one row to the next are [`+3\text{,}`][`+2\text{,}`] and [`+8\text{.}`] That's not a consistent pattern, but we need to consider rates of change between points. The rate of change between the first two points is [`\frac{-8-(-2)}{6-3}=-2\text{.}`] The rate of change between the next two points is [`\frac{-12-(-8)}{8-6}=-2\text{.}`] And the rate of change between the last two points is [`\frac{-20-(-12)}{12-8}=-2\text{.}`] So the rate of change, [`-2\text{,}`] is constant regardless of which pairs we choose. That means these pairs describe a linear relationship.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
